CPC Corp., a Taiwan state-run oil
company, bought 4 million barrels of Angolan crude for loading
in June via a tender, according to three traders who participate
in the market.  The company bought 2 million barrels each of Cabinda and
Nemba grades from Sonangol Holdings,  Chevron Corp. (CVX)  and China
International United Petroleum & Chemical Corp., or Unipec,
according to the people, who declined to be identified because
the information is confidential.  Details of the purchases are as follows:  To contact the reporter on this story:
